{Speech 4}{}{I'm Cassidy. And this is my bar.}
{Speech 4 Answer 7}{}{- Oh yeah? Well, I'm @pname@. And I've got no bar.}
{Speech 7}{}{Yeah? Tough luck. Well, either way - pleased to meet you. Let me offer you a drink on the house to mark the occasion.}
{Speech 7 Answer 8}{}{Thanks, I won't say no…}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{I don't drink, not a drop [Exit]}
{Speech 8}{}{Well, now we're acquainted… You're from far away, I reckon. Any interesting news?}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{What news could there be. Same as everywhere. The Wasteland. Shooting, robberies, scumbags…}
{Speech 8 Answer 10}{}{Nothing interesting. Maybe you can tell me something?}
{Speech 9}{}{A familiar picture.}
{Speech 9 Answer 10}{}{I'd rather just listen to you…}
{Speech 10}{}{And what do you want to hear?}
{Speech 10 Answer 11}{}{Well, for instance: did you know the Chosen One?}
{Speech 11}{}{Yes, I knew him. We traveled together.  But around here a lot of people know him. Some since childhood.}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{Will you tell me about it?}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{Oh yeah? Well, I'll go ask around some more…[Exit]}
{Speech 12}{}{Hmm, it'll be tough to tell it all. The journeys with him were quite eventful, though many of those events were all alike - the wasteland, shooting, scumbags….}
{Speech 12 Answer 13}{}{Go on…}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{Then I'd better be off. [Exit]}
{Speech 13}{}{…Well, after freeing his people from the Enclave tower, the Chosen One came back here, to his homeland. And I came with him. He knew well what gratitude was, and offered to let me stay here. Thanks to his efforts I have this bar. Here I found a wife and had a son. I'm getting too old to wander the wasteland, and here I have a steady income, and I'm always chatting with travelers like you.  My old bar, in the Vault City, I left to Cindy. A very clever woman. We keep in touch, write to each other.}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{What I really want to find out is - the Chosen One left, didn't he?}
{Speech 13 Answer Exit}{}{Very curious, but I have to go. Thanks for the story. [Exit]}
{Speech 14}{}{That's right.}
{Speech 14 Answer 15}{}{Do you know where to? Did he say anything?}
{Speech 15}{}{No, to both questions. He was pretty secretive, and didn't like sharing his plans. To talk, to discuss past events - sure, but he never revealed his plans to anyone.}
{Speech 15 Answer 16}{}{Hmm. I want to track him down…}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{I see. I'll be off then, thanks…[Exit]}
{Speech 16}{}{Hahaha [laughs for a while, slapping his hand on the bar counter]. Do you even have a rough idea how many people wanted to track him down in their day? Raiders, the mafia clans from Reno, the Enclave, Frank Horrigan… Well, you know how all that ended. Search if you like, of course, but the chances are slim, sorry.}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah, I understand. But I have to. Thanks, it was nice talking. [Exit]}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit*}{}{Alright, alright. We'll see what you all say when I find him. [Exit]}
{Speech 17}{}{Hmm, well, I've got one thing...Can you deliver a letter to the Vault City for Cindy?}
{Speech 17 Answer 18}{}{I can. I've carried worse...}
{Speech 18}{}{It's not urgent, but I'll need her reply. Will you take it on?}
{Speech 18 Answer 19}{}{Yes, of course.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Well, actually, I've got other plans, sorry.}
{Speech 19}{}{Good, I'll be waiting for your reply.}
{Speech 20}{}{How's that little letter of mine doing?}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{The letter's delivered, the reply's received. Here...}
{Speech 20 Answer 21*}{}{The letter's delivered, the reply's received. Here.}
{Speech 20 Answer 24}{}{The letter's delivered, Cindy said hi to you and promised to write a reply when she gets the chance.}
{Speech 20 Answer 22}{}{The letter's delivered, Cindy sent you her greetings and a letter, but I only managed to bring the greetings, unfortunately.}
{Speech 20 Answer 26}{}{Haven't managed to deliver it yet. I want to buy supplies before the road.}
{Speech 20 Answer 27}{}{I wanted to ask about something before I go.}
{Speech 20 Answer Exit}{}{Haven't had the time for it yet....}
{Speech 20 Answer 25}{}{Sorry, but the wasteland took my letter.}
{Speech 21}{}{Excellent, here, take this...}
{Speech 21 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you.[Exit]}
{Speech 22}{}{Hmm...Pity. Well, the wasteland's harsh, as everyone knows...}
{Speech 22 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you.[Exit]}
{Speech 24}{}{What, she couldn't even find a way to reply right away? Ugh. Such are our friends.}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah, from what I could tell, she took that letter with no joy at all...}
{Speech 24 Answer Exit*}{}{Nah, it's just that I came right in the middle of the day, she had a lot of customers. Relax, she'll reply.}
{Speech 23}{}{Sure, I'd go, of course...Hmm...But the truth is, I'm not a young man anymore. My heart's been acting up more and more. And besides - I've got a wife here, a child. No, I can't go with you. }
{Speech 23 Answer Exit}{}{Alright, I understand}
{Speech 25}{}{Hmm...Pity. Well, the wasteland's harsh, as everyone knows...}
{Speech 26}{}{Look at the shelves, pick what you want me to pour. The snack menu's hanging over there.}
{Speech 26 Answer Barter}{}{[Barter]}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{Actually I don't need anything. I wanted to ask about something...}
{Speech 26 Answer Exit}{}{Actually I'm not hungry.}
{Speech 26 Answer Barter*}{}{I want to buy something else...}
{Speech 26 Answer 27*}{}{Listen, there's something I wanted to find out...}
{Speech 26 Answer Exit*}{}{That's all, thanks.}
{Speech 27}{}{What do you need?}
{Speech 27 Answer 12}{}{Tell me again about the Chosen One.}
{Speech 27 Answer 23}{}{Listen, would you like to come with me to look for the Chosen One?}
{Speech 27 Answer 17}{}{You wouldn't happen to have any work? I'm broke...}
{Speech 27 Answer 28}{}{You wouldn't happen to have any work? I'm broke...}
{Speech 27 Answer 29}{}{Don't you need another letter delivered?}
{Speech 27 Answer 30}{}{Don't you need another letter delivered?}
{Speech 27 Answer 31}{}{Don't you need another letter delivered?}
{Speech 27 Answer 26}{}{Actually nothing. Better pour me a drink.}
{Speech 27 Answer Exit}{}{Alright, never mind. Bye.}
{Speech 28}{}{No, there's nothing at the moment.}
{Speech 28 Answer 26}{}{Then pour me a drink!}
{Speech 28 Answer 27}{}{Answer one more question...}
{Speech 28 Answer Exit}{}{Ugh... Nobody's got any!}
{Speech 29}{}{No, you just delivered the previous one not long ago.}
{Speech 29 Answer 26}{}{Then pour me a drink!}
{Speech 29 Answer 27}{}{Answer one more question...}
{Speech 29 Answer Exit}{}{Well, if not, then not, I'll be off.}
{Speech 30}{}{No, I've already hired a courier.}
{Speech 30 Answer 26}{}{Then pour me a drink!}
{Speech 30 Answer 27}{}{Answer one more question...}
{Speech 30 Answer Exit}{}{Damn. Next time wait for me!}
{Speech 31}{}{Oh! I was just thinking recently that I hadn't written to her in a while, and dashed off a letter. I just didn't have a courier. Will you take it on?}
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{Sure, why not.}
